error TS2531 Object is possibly 'null'.

https://typescript.tv/errors/#TS2531

To fix the problem, we can check if address is null by using optional chaining:

type Person = {
  address: {
    street: string;
    zipCode: number;
  } | null;
  name: string;
};

function logStreet(person: Person): void {
  console.log(person.address?.street);
}




Number(this.route.snapshot.paramMap.get('id'))

Or

this.route.paramMap.subscribe(param => {
      let id = +param.get('id');
})

